I'm proud to be an owner of an @AzukiZen, let alone a Gold trait. Just wish it didn't happen like this... 

Sorry to all those who lost their NFTs, as well as the buyers who are now unable to sell - We are all victims here.

@opensea - please remove the Suspicious Activity flags. You are not protecting anyone with this approach. All you are doing is punishing the buyers. The only one that wins is the scammer who stole and sold the NFT.

Not only do I feel guilty for the purchase, but @opensea flagged all stolen NFTs as "Reported for Suspicious Activity" - meaning the NFT cannot be listed, sold or offered on.

This is extraordinarily unfair for buyers who did nothing wrong.

Now I can't help but feel like I have "blood on my hands", despite having done nothing wrong.

I've reached out to the original owner (@AJFromDiscord) to try to find a solution. Unless @opensea considers reimbursing buyers of the stolen NFTs, there isn't much that can be done.
